{
  "stem": "428.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And in that camp, I was-- I don't know.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "This was in 1941.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And then, in that camp, I got sick of typhus.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And they took me.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "It was still in Krakow, it was a ghetto-- Ghetto C.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And they took me there and into a hospital.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And I was in that hospital, I don't know, two or three weeks.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And they liquidated.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "The liquidation of Krakow came in.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "They liquidated that town to completely killing everything what is alive.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And-- and-- while I was there, when I came-- when I walking into that camp, the same policeman what he took me into that camp, took me out of that hospital.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "His name was Wilek Pontel.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "He was a very, very healthy man.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "He was a Jewish policeman.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "By the Germans, they had Jewish policemen.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "They called them OD, Ordnungsdienst.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "So-- and he took me out of that camp.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "He paid money to a German policeman.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "There was wires, electric wires, and he took me out there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "But while going out, they liquidating already that Krakow.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "When you see they show you this.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "It was kids, babies.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "One year, two years.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "They used to take out the kids from the cribs by their legs and with their heads in the wall killing them.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was already in 1942.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This was already 1942. 1942.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then they took us to another camp.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The whole how you call it-- Fuhrer, the whole manager of that camp was Miller, an SS man by the name of Miller.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And over there they took me to work to the same place I was working.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Going out of the camp and working by a cement machine.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Cement machine operating.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then I used to sleep on that where we was working, too.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
